            <title>[HADOOP-6724] IPC doesn&apos;t properly handle IOEs thrown by socket factory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6724</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the socket factory throws an IOE inside setupIOStreams, then handleConnectionFailure will be called with socket still null, and thus generate an NPE on socket.close(). This ends up orphaning clients, etc.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
